codex
The main reward-routing issue is real and broader than just referral skimming: `TokenRewards` hard-depends on a mutable external referral hook during claim and share updates, so a malicious first initializer can turn normal reward accounting into a transfer/unstake DoS. I’m checking the referral and pricing interfaces now to tighten the remaining calls.
